              <div class="card-body" id="morning">
                <h5 class="card-title" id="itineraryTitle">Day 1</h5>
                <h6>MORNING</h6>
                <p class="card-text">Start your morning with a St. Charles staple, Colonial Cafe. Known in the community for their breakfast, you can also stop by there later in the day for their famous Kitchen Sink! 

                    Spend the rest of your morning into the afternoon at Pottawatomie Park. The park has mini golf, a pool, pedal boat rentals, playgrounds, sand volleyball courts and more.
                ​</p>
                  <h6>AFTERNOON</h6>
                <p class="card-text">The perfect spot for your family to grab a homemade fresh sandwich for lunch is Smitty's on the Corner. Then take a nice walk downtown to Rocket Fizz, where you can find shelves full of candy, soda pop and other vintage goodies.

                ​</p>
                  <h6>EVENING</h6>
                <p class="card-text">You are in the Suburbs of Chicago so obviously you must try a local pizza place! A must in St. Charles is Riverside Pizza. After you finish eating the cheesiest pizza in town, walk along the river path to Kimmer's Ice Cream. Known for exotic flavors, fun kid flavors and the famous Sparkle Cone™! 
                  ​</p>
              </div> 
